helpers.py`)\\n    31→- **Purpose**: Generate actual audio files for transcription testing\\n    32→- **Innovation**: No mocked audio data - all tests use real WAV files\\n    33→- **Capabilities**: Silence, tones, speech-like patterns with configurable durations\\n    34→\\n    35→```python\\n    36→# Real audio generation replaces mocked data\\n    37→audio_data = audio_generator.generate_silence(2.0)\\n    38→audio_file = audio_generator.create_wav_file(audio_data, \\\"test.wav\\\")\\n    39→text, language = await transcription_service.transcribe_audio(audio_file, \\\"en\\\")\\n    40→```\\n    41→\\n    42→### 2. Real Transcription Validation (`tests/test_transcription_real.py`)\\n    43→- **Purpose**: Validate actual Whisper model behavior\\n    44→- **15 tests** covering real transcription scenarios\\n    45→- **Key Validations**:\\n    46→  - Silence → minimal output\\n    47→  - Tones → minimal output\\n    48→  - Speech-like audio → reasonable output\\n    49→  - Error handling with corrupted files\\n    50→  - Performance benchmarks\\n    51→\\n    52→### 3. Integration Command Testing (`tests/test_commands_real.py`)\\n    53→- **Purpose**: Test commands with real services, not mocks\\n    54→- **11 tests** validating complete command workflows\\n    55→- **Real Validations**:\\n    56→  - Actual project creation and file system operations\\n    57→  - Real state persistence and retrieval\\n    58→  - Complete multi-command workflows\\n    59→  - Error scenarios with real error conditions\\n    60→\\n    61→### 4. End-to-End Pipeline Testing (`tests/test_end_to_end.py`)\\n    62→- **Purpose**: Validate complete user workflows from start to finish\\n    63→- **5 tests** covering full system integration\\n    64→- **Complete Pipelines**:\\n    65→  - Voice audio → Whisper transcription → file storage → user feedback\\n    66→  - Multi-language processing with real translation\\n    67→  - Error handling across the entire pipeline\\n    68→  - State persistence across service restarts\\n    69→\\n    70→### 5. Performance Benchmarking (`tests/test_performance.py`)\\n    71→- **Purpose**: Monitor real system performance characteristics\\n    72→- **8 tests** measuring actual performance\\n    73→- **Benchmarks**:\\n    74→  - Whisper model loading times\\n    75→  - Transcription speed across audio types\\n    76→  - Memory usage monitoring\\n    77→  - Service operation performance\\n    78→  - Concurrent processing capabilities\\n    79→\\n    80→## Key Achievements\\n    81→\\n    82→### ✅ Eliminated Mock Abuse\\n    83→\\n    84→**Before:**\\n    85→```python\\n    86→@patch('whisper.load_model')\\n    87→def test_transcribe_audio(self, mock_load_model):\\n    88→    mock_model = Mock()\\n    89→    mock_model.transcribe.return_value = {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Fake result\\\"}\\n    90→    # Tests NOTHING about real transcription!\\n    91→```\\n    92→\\n    93→**After:**\\n    94→```python\\n    95→async def test_transcribe_silence_produces_minimal_output(self, real_transcription_service):\\n    96→    silence_data = audio_generator.generate_silence(2.0)\\n    97→    audio_file = audio_generator.create_wav_file(silence_data, \\\"silence.wav\\\")\\n    98→    text, language = await real_transcription_service.transcribe_audio(audio_file, \\\"en\\\")\\n    99→    assert len(text.strip()) <= 10  # Real validation of Whisper behavior\\n   100→```\\n   101→\\n   102→### ✅ Real Integration Testing\\n   103→\\n   104→Complete workflows tested end-to-end:\\n   105→1. Project creation through actual command system\\n   106→2. Real audio file processing through Whisper\\n   107→3. Actual file I/O and state persistence\\n   108→4. Error handling with real error conditions\\n   109→\\n   110→### ✅ Performance Validation\\n   111→\\n   112→Real performance characteristics measured:\\n   113→- Model loading: < 30 seconds (enforced)\\n   114→- Transcription speed: < 3x real-time (enforced)\\n   115→- Memory usage: < 500MB for tiny model