## 🔍 What Went Wrong

The python-test-auditor agent was misled by the presence of good test files and documentation. It saw `TEST_STRATEGY.md` describing "Death to Mock Abuse" and files like `test_commands_real.py` with real testing, and incorrectly concluded the entire test suite was already transformed. It failed to examine `test_commands.py` which still contains 100% mock-based tests.

## 🎯 Why It Happened

**Primary Cause**: The agent lacked explicit instructions to audit EVERY test file individually
**Contributing Factors**:
- No requirement to list and examine all test files systematically
- Agent assumed good documentation meant all tests were good

